  "explanation": "The defendant is a first-time offender who committed a non-violent financial crime involving $25,000, with partial restitution already made, which demonstrates intent to rectify the harm. While embezzlement is a serious breach of trust, the guidelines for a first-time white-collar offense of this magnitude generally favor a balance of rehabilitation and punitive measures. The outburst from the spectator is irrelevant to the legal sentencing process and will not influence the verdict. Taking into account the mitigating factor of the lack of a criminal record and the partial restitution, a sentence of 8 months incarceration provides sufficient punishment and deterrent effect without being excessive.",
